      "text": "Five defendants pleaded guilty to federal firearms offenses while a federal grand jury indicted eight others in an international firearms trafficking conspiracy that funneled illegally obtained weapons from New Hampshire through the Akwesasne Mohawk Indian Reservation in New York.\n\nICE @HSIBuffalo, NY, and @ATFHQ led the investigation that identified about 50 firearms potentially trafficked from New Hampshire to Canada through Vermont and New York, several of which were recovered at various crime scenes, to include kidnapping and attempted murder, in Canada.",
